<p>05.16.14</p>
<div class="newsbody"><p>We are&nbsp;thrilled to announce that Anna Maria Tremonti will host our 2014 Spring Fundraiser at the Bloor Cinema&mdash;a screening of&nbsp;<strong>Everybody&rsquo;s Children</strong>,&nbsp;a documentary film about the journey of two refugee youth seeking asylum alone in Canada.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Anna Maria Tremonti can be heard weekday mornings across Canada as the host of&nbsp;The Current&nbsp;on CBC Radio One. She has a distinguished background in journalism, with years of experience in both television and radio.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Following the screening,&nbsp;Anna Maria will host a panel discussion on the plight of unaccompanied refugee teens. Panel participants will include former Matthew House resident Salieu from Sierra Leone, who is featured in the film, and others who have journeyed the same path alone.</p>
<p>Join us for an informative evening&nbsp;about the plight of refugee claimants in Canada and learn how you can support our work of making a positive difference. Tickets are available by <strong><a href="http://www.matthewhouse.ca/index.cfm?eventid=6968&amp;pagepath=Events&amp;id=49964#event6968">clicking here</a>.</strong></p>
